This paper deals with the problem of constructing phylogenetic networks, which is a topic in computational biology. However, the paper's approach involves graph theory and algorithmic techniques, making it relevant to computer science. The paper's focus on fixed parameter tractability suggests that it may belong to the cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) or cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) sub-categories. The use of graph theory suggests that it may also belong to the cs.CG (Computational Geometry) or cs.LG (Computational Learning Theory) sub-categories. Finally, the paper's application to phylogenetics suggests that it may also belong to the cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) sub-category.
